At line 226-231, `DeleteRecompiledNodesInCHIROptEffectMap` iterates over `recompiledNodes` (which are `Ptr<AST::Decl>`) and accesses `decl->rawMangleName` and `mainDecl->desugarDecl->rawMangleName`. These are AST pointer dereferences!

But wait — this is called from `UpdateCachedInfo()` which is called from `UpdateAndWriteCachedInfoToDisk()`. The V2 proposal says `ReleaseASTData()` is called AFTER `UpdateAndWriteCachedInfoToDisk()`. So at the time `DeleteRecompiledNodesInCHIROptEffectMap` runs, the AST is still alive. This is correct.

However, after `ReleaseASTData()`, `declsToBeReCompiled` still holds dangling pointers. If the `IncrementalCompilerInstance` destructor or any other code accesses `declsToBeReCompiled` after `ReleaseASTData()`, it would be a use-after-free. But since `declsToBeReCompiled` is private and only used in the methods I've already checked, this is safe as long as `ReleaseASTData()` is the last operation before destruction.

Also at line 399-400:
```cpp
for (auto pkg : GetSourcePackages()) {
    Sema::CollectCompilerAddedDeclUsage(*pkg, cachedInfo.semaInfo);
}
```

This is in `UpdateCachedInfo()` — it accesses `GetSourcePackages()` which returns `srcPkgs` pointers. Again, this runs before `ReleaseASTData()`, so it's safe.

Now I have enough information to write the final report. Let me also check one more thing — the `ExecuteFrontendByDriver` path:

<!-- chunk-boundary -->

The V2 proposal only shows integration in `ExecuteFrontend` (the standalone frontend path). But `ExecuteFrontendByDriver` is the Driver path where the instance is passed by reference and later deleted asynchronously. The V2 proposal doesn't show `ReleaseASTData()` being called in this path.

This is a significant omission — the Driver path is the primary compilation path (when using `cjc` as opposed to `cjc-frontend`). Without `ReleaseASTData()` in this path, Phase 2 memory savings won't apply to the most common compilation scenario.

Moreover, the Driver path at line 207 uses `std::async(DeleteInstance, instance)` to delete the instance asynchronously. If `ReleaseASTData()` were added to `ExecuteFrontendByDriver` (after `UpdateAndWriteCachedInfoToDisk()`), it would free AST memory synchronously before the backend toolchain runs, which is the ideal behavior — AST memory is freed while the linker/assembler runs.

